From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 15:04:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 33/33] web-app: hover popovers with avatars for read-by status
 and reactions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Reveal a small popover when hovering the delivery-status icon or the
reactions cluster of a message, so the "who read this / who reacted"
information is available without opening the Message Info or Reactions
dialog.

- Read-by: hovering the outgoing delivery-status icon shows the contacts
  who have read the message, each with their avatar, name and a relative
  timestamp ("2 minutes ago"); the absolute time is on the row's title.
  When there are no read receipts yet it falls back to a short status
  label (Sending… / Delivered / Read / Failed to send). Data comes from
  getMessageReadReceipts and refreshes on the MsgRead event, and is only
  fetched once the popover is first opened.
- Reactions: hovering the reactions cluster lists everyone who reacted
  with their avatar, name and the emoji they picked, grouped by the
  core's most-used-first ordering. Clicking still opens the full
  ReactionsDialog.

Both share a new PeopleHoverInfo component (the hover trigger, the card
shell, a lazy contacts-by-id fetch and a relative-time helper). Adds the
untranslated labels Sending…/Delivered/Failed to send and "Reacted with
%1$s".
